<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870608-0035 </DOCNO><HL> American ExplorationWill Buy a Britoil UnitIn U.S. for $88 Million</HL><DD> 06/08/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AXCOTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Exploration Co. agreed to buy the U.S. oil subsidiary of Britoil PLC for about $88 million.    American Exploration expects the purchase to double its oil and gas reserves, a spokesman said. American Exploration buys producing oil and gas properties and finances the transactions through the limited partnerships it manages.    Under terms, American Exploration will buy interests varying from 5% to 35% in about 200 oil and gas fields primarily in the Texas and Louisiana Gulf Coast area, Oklahoma and the Rocky Mountain states. The purchase would include oil and gas reserves totaling about 20 million barrels of oil equivalent.    American Exploration, which now has about eight million barrels of oil equivalent, said the specific number of reserves the investors and the company would receive hasn't yet been determined.    The transaction is &quot;an attractive investment opportunity,&quot; the spokesman said.    Britoil explores for and produces oil. </TEXT></DOC>